-- Harvard Defeats Bucknell 35-7 to Stay Undefeated Atop Ivy League
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-10-14T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-14/harvard-defeats-bucknell-35-7-to-stay-undefeated-atop-ivy-league.html
Colton Chapple threw for two
touchdowns and ran for two others as  Harvard University  defeated
Bucknell University 35-7 to remain undefeated in college
football.  In other  Ivy League  Conference contests yesterday, it was
Lafayette 20, Yale 10; Princeton 19, Brown 0; Cornell 41,
Monmouth 38; Pennsylvania 24, Columbia 20; and Sacred Heart 27,
Dartmouth 10.  At Harvard Stadium in Cambridge,  Massachusetts , Chapple ran
six yards for a touchdown in the first quarter and then
connected with Cameron Brate on a 14-yard scoring pass and Kyle
Juszczyk on a 59-yard pass in the second quarter. Andrew Fischer
added a 58-yard touchdown run to give the Crimson (5-0) a 28-0
halftime lead.  Chapple scored on a 59-yard run in the third quarter to end
Harvardâ€™s scoring, while Jeremiah Young had a one-yard score for
the Bison (1-5) with 59 seconds left in the game.  The Harvard quarterback completed 11 of 18 passing attempts
for 189 yards, two touchdowns and one interception. He also
carried eight times for 120 yards and two touchdowns.  Brandon Wesley went 20-for-28 for 189 yards and one
interception.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in  Washington  at 
